ğŸ¬ Customer Sentiment Analysis
Domain-Adaptive Transformer Models for Feedback Understanding

ğŸ” Overview

This project reframes sentiment analysis as a customer insight and feedback understanding problem rather than a simple text classification task.

Instead of relying solely on generic pretrained language models, the system adapts transformer representations to the movie-review domain, capturing:

Domain-specific vocabulary usage

Subtle sentiment cues (sarcasm, irony)

Contextual sentiment shifts in long-form feedback

An end-to-end NLP pipeline was developed and deployed in a production-like environment using Docker and Azure App Service.

ğŸ¯ Problem Motivation

Generic pretrained transformers often underperform on domain-specific customer feedback due to:

Vocabulary mismatch

Over-reliance on surface-level sentiment words

Poor handling of mixed or delayed sentiment expression

This project evaluates whether domain-adaptive pretraining (MLM) improves downstream sentiment classification reliability.

ğŸ“‚ Dataset
Large Movie Review Dataset v1.0 (IMDB)

Key Characteristics

50,000 labeled reviews

25,000 training

25,000 testing

Balanced polarity (positive / negative)

50,000 unlabeled reviews for unsupervised pretraining

Train/test splits contain disjoint movies (prevents leakage)

Maximum 30 reviews per movie to reduce correlation bias

